{"created": "2025-06-05T07:27:49.738078+00:00", "modified": "2025-06-05T07:32:12.186718+00:00", "id": 15004761, "conceptrecid": "15004760", "doi": "10.5281/zenodo.15004761", "conceptdoi": "10.5281/zenodo.15004760", "doi_url": "https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.15004761", "metadata": {"title": "SIMCODE clinical trials data", "doi": "10.5281/zenodo.15004761", "publication_date": "2025-03-11", "description": "<p>Patient-level data on primary and secondary endpoints of a multicenter randomized controlled trial investigating Simvastatin (40 mg/d) or placebo as add-on to escitalopram in patients with comorbid major depression and obesity.</p>\n<p>We hypothesized that Simvastatin add-on to standard antidepressant Escitalopram will improve depression to a greater extent than add-on placebo in patients with comorbid obesity and major depression. <span><span>The primary outcome was change in Montgomery-&Aring;sberg Depression Rating Scale (MADRS) score from baseline (week 0) to week 12. </span></span>We randomized 161 obese MDD patients at 9 recruiting centers in Germany to either Simvastatin or placebo as add-on to Escitalopram for 12 weeks.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>ClinicalTrials.gov Identifier: NCT04301271.</p>", "access_right": "open", "creators": [{"name": "Otte, Christian", "affiliation": "Charit\u00e9 - Universit\u00e4tsmedizin Berlin", "orcid": "0000-0002-4051-997X"}, {"name": "Chae, Woo Ri", "affiliation": "Charit\u00e9 - Universit\u00e4tsmedizin Berlin", "orcid": "0000-0002-6326-8333"}, {"name": "Gold, Stefan", "affiliation": "Charite Universit\u00e4tsmedizin Berlin", "orcid": "0000-0001-5188-4799"}], "related_identifiers": [{"identifier": "10.1136/bmjopen-2020-040119", "relation": "isDescribedBy", "resource_type": "publication-article", "scheme": "doi"}, {"identifier": "10.1001/jamapsychiatry.2025.0801", "relation": "isPublishedIn", "resource_type": "publication-article", "scheme": "doi"}], "resource_type": {"title": "Dataset", "type": "dataset"}, "license": {"id": "cc-by-4.0"},